<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1901-07-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1901-07-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="280" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d280">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Iddings</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-07-31"><hi rend="italic">July 31,
                                1901</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 32.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: * * * I inclose copy of a letter<note n="a" xml:id="d280fna">Not printed.</note> from the attorneys of the
                            United States Lloyds, who are anxious to ascertain exactly what the
                            relations between Italy and the Sultan Osman Mahmud are.</p>
                        <p>You will investigate the matter and report.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>